 <p class="text-[11px] font-black text-brandOrange uppercase tracking-widest mb-2">Quick Answer</p>
 <p class="text-slate-700 text-lg leading-relaxed"><strong>What is a power bank?</strong> A power bank is a portable battery pack that charges devices on the go. Key specs include capacity (measured in mAh or Wh), power output (watts via PD 3.1), and cell type (semi-solid-state or Li-polymer). WOWOHCOOL manufactures power banks from 5,000mAh to 27,000mAh with PD 3.1 up to 140W.</p>
 </div>

 <section id="capacity-rated" class="mb-16">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">1. What Is the Difference Between Cell and Rated Capacity?</h2>
 <div class="bg-brandBlue/10 border border-brandBlue/30 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
 <h4 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3"><svg class="icon-calculator mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 384 512">
 <path d="M64 0C28.7 0 0 28.7 0 64L0 448c0 35.3 28.7 64 64 64l256 0c35.3 0 64-28.7 64-64l0-384c0-35.3-28.7-64-64-64L64 0zM96 64l192 0c17.7 0 32 14.3 32 32l0 32c0 17.7-14.3 32-32 32L96 160c-17.7 0-32-14.3-32-32l0-32c0-17.7 14.3-32 32-32zm16 168a24 24 0 1 1 -48 0 24 24 0 1 1 48 0zm80 24a24 24 0 1 1 0-48 24 24 0 1 1 0 48zm128-24a24 24 0 1 1 -48 0 24 24 0 1 1 48 0zM88 352a24 24 0 1 1 0-48 24 24 0 1 1 0 48zm128-24a24 24 0 1 1 -48 0 24 24 0 1 1 48 0zm80 24a24 24 0 1 1 0-48 24 24 0 1 1 0 48zM64 424c0-13.3 10.7-24 24-24l112 0c13.3 0 24 10.7 24 24s-10.7 24-24 24L88 448c-13.3 0-24-10.7-24-24zm232-24c13.3 0 24 10.7 24 24s-10.7 24-24 24-24-10.7-24-24 10.7-24 24-24z" fill="currentColor"/>
 </svg>The Real Capacity Formula</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">Don't trust the number on the box alone. Cell capacity and real output are different. Know this gap for accurate product specs and happy customers. Here is how to find real output:</p>
 <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4 text-center font-mono text-sm">
 <span class="text-brandBlue font-bold">(mAh × 3.7V × Efficiency) / Output V = Real Output</span>
 </div>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-3">Example: A 10,000mAh power bank with 85% efficiency charging at 5V provides:</p>
 <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4 text-center font-mono text-sm">
 <span class="text-brandOrange font-bold">(10,000 × 3.7 × 0.85) / 5 = 6,290mAh</span>
 </div>
 </div>
 
 <div class="space-y-6">
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-3">Capacity (mAh)</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">mAh measures the total energy storage of a power bank. This is the key spec for how many charges you get. More mAh means more charges but also more weight and size.</p>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">A 10,000mAh power bank gives 2-3 full phone charges in ideal conditions. Real-world results vary by device battery size, age, and charging conditions.</p>
 <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-3">
 <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-slate-200 text-xs">5,000mAh = 1-2 charges</span>
 <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-slate-200 text-xs">10,000mAh = 2-3 charges</span>
 <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-slate-200 text-xs">20,000mAh = 4-6 charges</span>
 <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-slate-200 text-xs">26,800mAh = 6-8 charges</span>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-3">Input/Output Power (W)</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">Wattage (W) sets charging speed. The formula: <strong>Watts = Volts x Amps</strong>. An 18W power bank charges a phone much faster than a 5W one.</p>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">For fast charging, pick 18W, 30W, 45W, or 65W+ output. Higher wattage lets you charge laptops but creates more heat and costs more.</p>
 <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-3">
 <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-slate-200 text-xs">5W = Standard charging</span>
 <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-slate-200 text-xs">18W = Fast charging (QC 3.0)</span>
 <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-slate-200 text-xs">65W = Laptop charging</span>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-3">Ports & Connectivity</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">Modern power banks offer multiple port types: USB-A, USB-C, and Lightning input. USB-C with Power Delivery (PD) is the fastest and most versatile option, supporting bidirectional charging.</p>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Multiple ports allow simultaneous charging of several devices. When using multiple ports, output power is typically distributed, reducing charging speed per device.</p>
 </div>
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-3">Conversion Rate</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">The actual usable capacity is 60-80% of the stated mAh due to energy loss during voltage conversion and heat generation. A 10,000mAh power bank typically delivers 6,000-8,000mAh to your device.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 
