 </tr>
 </tbody>
 </table>
 </div>
 </div>

 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-4">Step 2: Apply the Conversion Formula</h3>
 <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4 border border-slate-200 mb-4">
 <p class="text-slate-900 font-mono text-sm"><strong>Usable Capacity = Stated mAh × 0.70 (conversion rate) × (Power Bank Voltage / Device Voltage)</strong></p>
 </div>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">For example, a 10,000mAh power bank (3.7V) charging an iPhone 15 (3.87V battery):</p>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm font-mono bg-white rounded p-3">10,000 × 0.70 × (3.7/3.87) = <strong>6,699 mAh actual output</strong></p>
 </div>

 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
 <h3 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-4">Step 3: Match Capacity to Use Case</h3>
 <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
 <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5 text-center">
