 <p class="text-slate-600 text-xs">1 full charge for most smartphones. Fits in jacket pockets. Lightweight at 150-250g.</p>
 </div>
 <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5 text-center">
 <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3">Business Travel</h3>
 <p class="text-3xl font-black text-brandOrange mb-2">10,000-20,000mAh</p>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-xs">2-4 full charges. Charges laptop once. Fits in laptop bags. Weight: 300-450g.</p>
 </div>
 <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5 text-center">
 <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3">Extended Travel</h3>
 <p class="text-3xl font-black text-brandOrange mb-2">20,000-26,800mAh</p>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-xs">4-6 full phone charges. Multiple device support. May require airline approval for 100Wh+.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>

 <div class="bg-brandBlue/5 border border-brandBlue/20 rounded-xl p-6">
 <h4 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3"><svg class="icon-plane mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 576 512">
 <path d="M520 200c30.9 0 56 25.1 56 56s-25.1 56-56 56l-127.3 0-159.2 173.6c-6.1 6.6-14.6 10.4-23.6 10.4l-43.7 0c-10.9 0-18.6-10.7-15.2-21.1l54.3-162.9-99.7 0-52.8 66c-3 3.8-7.6 6-12.5 6l-19.8 0c-10.4 0-18-9.8-15.5-19.9L32 256 5 147.9C2.4 137.8 10.1 128 20.5 128l19.8 0c4.9 0 9.5 2.2 12.5 6l52.8 66 99.7 0-54.3-162.9C147.6 26.7 155.3 16 166.2 16l43.7 0c9 0 17.5 3.8 23.6 10.4L392.7 200 520 200z" fill="currentColor"/>
 </svg>Airline Regulations</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">According to <a href="https://www.iata.org/en/programs/cargo/dgr/lithium-batteries/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandOrange hover:underline">IATA regulations</a>, passengers may carry power banks up to 100Wh without airline approval. For 100-160Wh, airline approval is required. Anything above 160Wh is prohibited for passenger flights.</p>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Quick math: A 26,800mAh power bank at 3.7V = 99.16Wh (within limit). A 30,000mAh = 111Wh (requires approval).</p>
 </div>
 </section>

 <section id="common-mistakes" class="mb-16">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">6. Common Power Bank Mistakes to Avoid</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6">Based on industry data and user feedback, these are the most common buying and usage mistakes. They lead to poor results, safety risks, or wasted money. Avoid these to meet customer needs and safety rules.</p>
 
 <div class="space-y-4">
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 flex gap-4">
 <span class="text-3xl font-black text-brandOrange/30">01</span>
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Ignoring Real Capacity vs Stated Capacity</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Many buyers assume 10,000mAh means 10,000mAh of usable power. In reality, conversion losses mean you only get 6,000-8,000mAh. Always calculate actual output using the conversion formula above.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 flex gap-4">
 <span class="text-3xl font-black text-brandOrange/30">02</span>
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Buying Based on Price Alone</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Extremely cheap power banks often use recycled battery cells, inferior circuitry, and fake capacity ratings. According to <a href="https://www.which.co.uk/reviews/power-banks/article/power-bank-capacity-explained-aDvKf8d7mJhR" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandOrange hover:underline">Which? research</a>, budget power banks under $15 frequently fail basic safety tests.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 flex gap-4">
 <span class="text-3xl font-black text-brandOrange/30">03</span>
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Mismatched Charging Standards</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">A power bank with QC 3.0 won't fast charge an iPhone (which uses PD). Similarly, VOOC requires specific cables. Verify your devices support the power bank's charging protocols before purchase.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 flex gap-4">
 <span class="text-3xl font-black text-brandOrange/30">04</span>
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Overlooking Input Power</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Fast charging your phone means nothing if the power bank takes 12+ hours to recharge. Look for input power of 18W+ via USB-C PD for reasonable recharge times (4-6 hours for 10,000mAh).</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 flex gap-4">
 <span class="text-3xl font-black text-brandOrange/30">05</span>
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Ignoring Watt-Hour Limits for Air Travel</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Many travelers discover their 30,000mAh power bank is confiscated at security because it exceeds the 100Wh limit. Always check airline regulations before packing.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 flex gap-4">
 <span class="text-3xl font-black text-brandOrange/30">06</span>
 <div>
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-2">Using Damaged or Swollen Batteries</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Signs of battery swelling (warped casing, difficulty inserting into devices) indicate dangerous chemical reactions. Immediately discontinue use and dispose properly at certified e-waste facilities.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

